summary: ‘Captain Marvel’ Goes Higher Further and Faster For the MCU
title: ‘Captain Marvel’ Goes Higher Further and Faster For the MCU
body:
Sorry to burst your bubble, haters, but Captain Marvel is really good.

With all the controversy surrounding Captain Marvel, created by internet trolls, it was refreshing to watch the film and see how wrong they were about it. Captain Marvel has been labeled a feminist film, and it is, but it does so without dragging men down. Instead, the film focuses on women empowerment, sisterhood, and…

summary: So apparently white men are offended at Brie Larson for "saying she doesn't want white men to see the movie" which tells me a)...
body:
So apparently white men are offended at Brie Larson for “saying she doesn’t want white men to see the movie” which tells me a) they have zero reading comprehension and therefore b) just want an excuse to hate Brie Larson.

Because if it’s based on this article, which I have read myself, what she was saying was that she wanted *critics* to not be overwhelmingly white male. Critics, as in the members of press that see the movie and rate it. Nothing she said had anything to do with the general audience.

The fact that a large amount of white men took what she said so wrong is very telling about the men.
